<!-- Tuple Pattern -->
	<chapter id="ref.patterns.tuple">
		<title>Tuple Pattern</title>
		<section id="ref.patterns.tuple.body">
			<para>
				In Orc pattern matching, when a value is compared to a tuple, the entire tuple must
				be matched exactly to be considered a successful pattern match.
			</para>
			<para><emphasis role="strong">EBNF</emphasis>: <emphasis>P ::= ( P , ... , P )</emphasis></para>
		</section>
		
		 <section id="ref.patterns.tuple.examples">
		  <title>Examples</title>
		  <examplescript/>
		  <example caption="Filtering" id="ref.patterns.tuple.examples.one">
<programlisting><![CDATA[
{- Signal for each of the input tuples that have their first value as true -}
(false, true, true) | (true, false, false) | (false, false, false) >(true, _, _)> signal
]]></programlisting>
		  </example>
		</section>
		
